    "name": "The Machine In The Garden",
    "profile": "The Machine in the Garden is a gothic/darkwave duo featuring [a=Roger Fracé] and [a=Summer Bowman]. Since their formation, Roger and Summer have developed and advanced their unique style through years of collaborating and intertwining their musical tastes.\r\n\r\nThe band's first release was the 1994 [i]Veils and Shadows EP[/i]. Initially a solo endeavor by Roger Fracé, the debut EP blended the dark elements of goth with new wave and industrial tinges. However, folded within the songs were melodies of a more classical nature.\r\n\r\nThe band's sound further evolved with the addition of musician Summer Bowman. Her enchanting voice lent an ethereal quality to the music on the duo's first full-length recording, [i]Underworld[/i], in 1997. The dark electronics of the debut EP, which garnered acclaim from press and radio, were still there, but multi-layered with an atmospheric mood and style, giving the CD an original sound transcending pre-existing genres.\r\n\r\nFollowing a string of successful singl",
